      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/b5a626/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2024-01-09T13:43:41.751Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Coach Jack got me a \u2018Plan: The Serious Italian\u2019 plan. I synchronize the trainings with intervals.icu.<br>\nThere in the calender view you can see the current and next week of training. Today I recognized, that my fitness score won\u2019t improve if I follow the planned workouts:</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e466c2d94a62efb9da6289a4ba41e283a5919683.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/e466c2d94a62efb9da6289a4ba41e283a5919683\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/e/e466c2d94a62efb9da6289a4ba41e283a5919683_2_690x207.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"wAx1JuAqGkgNPRGvTNqXFPYz0Px\" width=\"690\" height=\"207\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/e/e466c2d94a62efb9da6289a4ba41e283a5919683_2_690x207.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/e/e466c2d94a62efb9da6289a4ba41e283a5919683_2_1035x310.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/e/e466c2d94a62efb9da6289a4ba41e283a5919683_2_1380x414.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/e/e466c2d94a62efb9da6289a4ba41e283a5919683_2_10x10.png\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1637\u00d7492 83 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>I think the algorithm intervals uses depends on the TSS score. High TSS moves the form curve up, medium/low intensity workouts will lead to a constant curve == no fitness improvement (?)</p>\n<p>How can I determine whether training is effective?</p>",
