      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/90db22/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2024-01-09T14:36:11.906Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Your fitness number has nothing to do whether training is effective or not. And with a TSS of 300 you end up with a fitness score in the 40s. (300/7)<br>\nIf you want to increase fitness number, you have to increase the Load (TSS).<br>\nYou can do this by adding volume or adding intensity.</p>\n<p><a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/medtechcd\">@MedTechCD</a> did a good job in describing the fitness page and their values. I recommend you read these posts in intervals forum <a href=\"https://forum.intervals.icu/t/fitness-page-a-guide-to-getting-started/17702/3\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">FITNESS PAGE - a guide to getting started - #3 by MedTechCD - Guide - Intervals.icu Forum</a></p>",
