      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2024-01-10T10:21:06.833Z",
      "cooked": "<p>One thing Dr Seiler points out for example is 20 minutes at FTP (100%) after a 20 minute warmup is totally different stress than 20 minutes at FTP(100%) at the end of a hard 4 hour ride.  So from a math perspective TSS != TSS (Training Stress).  Still from a rough broad perspective, TSS is a fine metric especially when used correctly as you are using it.</p>",
