      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/90db22/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2024-01-10T20:08:15.244Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Yeah, that\u2019s true too. There are studies which show that your aerobic and anaerobic threshold will move downwards with higher fatigue during an exercise, especially if you do high intensity stuff. So for example you do a sweetspot interval in the first hour, and then you do the same power in the second or third hour, it maybe becomes a threshold interval. The calculated training stress is the same for those parts, but it\u2019s not the same stress for your body, yes.</p>",
